Title : [A rare cause of chronic respiratory insufficiency: arthrogryposis in adults].
Date : 1997
Publication_type : Journal Article
Abstract : Arthrogryposis is a congenital disease leading to multiple joint ankylosis in utero observed as sequellae at birth. Deformation of the chest produces respiratory failure usually seen at birth. We report a case in an adult which required intermittent nocturnal positive pressure nasal ventilation.
